EThekwini Mayor Mxolisi Kaunda has condemned the killing of
two municipal game rangers at Silverglen Nature Reserve in Chatsworth on Thursday. Preliminary investigation reveals that the two employees,
who were on duty died from a hail of bullets while sitting in a patrol vehicle.
The motive for the killing is unknown at this stage and the police are still
investigating. Mayor Kaunda has
called on the police to speed up the investigation so that those responsible for
the murder are apprehended. "We condemn the ambush attack on our game rangers who
were on duty patrolling the nature reserve. Killings of this nature are not
common in our natural resources and we have instructed officials to intensify
safety and security in all our nature reserves. We also want to urge members of
the community to come forward with any information that might lead to the
apprehension of the perpetrators,‚Äù said Kaunda. The Mayor has
conveyed his heartfelt condolences to the families of the deceased.